Records of the Office of Institutional Research and Planning

This series contains the website for the Factbook, which is made up of statistics on personnel for New York University dating back to 2008. Since 2015, the university used Tableau, a visualization software, to display statistics and also compiled statistics in PDF form. The statistics document enrollment and admission rates, enrollment by race and sex, graduation and rentention rates, financial aid, faculty and staff statistics by race and sex, and tuition.
Crawls were expanded to include PDFs and Tableau. The public link to the Tableau table was added to the web archives to attempt to achieve a more navigable crawl but was not added to the finding aid.

Due to technical or privacy issues, archived websites may not be exact copies of the original website at the time of the web crawl. Certain file types will not be captured dependent on how they are embedded in the site. Other parts of websites that the crawler has difficulty capturing includes Javascript, streaming content, database-driven content, and highly interactive content. Full-Text searches of archived websites are available at https://archive-it.org/organizations/567.
